--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Discharge module for `decode-rel-resp-‚ČÖŠīī-atomic-compound-0E` from
-- `RespIso/AtomicCompound.agda`.
--
-- ## Goal
--
-- Given an atomic `f : HomTerm A B` (one of `id, őĽ‚áí, őĽ‚áź, ŌĀ‚áí, ŌĀ‚áź, őĪ‚áí,
-- őĪ‚áź, ŌÉ` ‚ÄĒ the Agen case is handled separately by edge-count
-- arithmetic) and a compound `g : HomTerm A B` (i.e. `_‚ąė_` or `_‚äó‚āĀ_`)
-- whose translation has zero edges, plus an iso `‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę`,
-- show `decode-rel f ‚ČąTerm decode-rel g`.
--
-- ## Why `g` is "structural"
--
-- Edge counts are additive across `_‚ąė_` and `_‚äó‚āĀ_`:
--
--   * `nE ‚ü™ h ‚ąė k ‚üę  = nE ‚ü™ h ‚üę + nE ‚ü™ k ‚üę`
--   * `nE ‚ü™ h ‚äó‚āĀ k ‚üę = nE ‚ü™ h ‚üę + nE ‚ü™ k ‚üę`
--
-- and `nE ‚ü™ Agen _ ‚üę ‚Č° 1`.  So `nE ‚ü™ g ‚üę ‚Č° 0` propagates inductively:
-- every sub-term of `g` has zero edges, which rules out every `Agen`
-- node anywhere inside `g`.  We encode this as the `Structural`
-- predicate below ‚ÄĒ a syntactic witness "no `Agen` subterm" ‚ÄĒ and
-- prove the equivalence `nE ‚ü™ g ‚üę ‚Č° 0  ‚ÜĒ  Structural g`.
--
-- Both `f` (a structural atomic constructor) and `g` (a structural
-- compound) therefore live in the fragment generated by
-- `id, őĽ‚áí, őĽ‚áź, ŌĀ‚áí, ŌĀ‚áź, őĪ‚áí, őĪ‚áź, ŌÉ` under `_‚ąė_, _‚äó‚āĀ_`.  At the level
-- of `FreeMonoidal` this is exactly the *coherence fragment*: the
-- symmetric monoidal coherence theorem (Mac Lane + braiding) says any
-- two morphisms of the same type in this fragment whose underlying
-- permutations agree are `‚ČąTerm`-equal.  The iso `‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę`
-- forces the underlying permutations to agree (both hypergraphs have
-- 0 edges, so they are entirely characterised by their boundary
-- permutations, and the iso provides a ŌÜ matching dom/cod up to
-- relabelling).
--
-- Constructive discharge requires the symmetric-monoidal coherence
-- solver (the existing `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver` covers
-- the Mac Lane fragment but not ŌÉ; see
-- `Hypergraph.Completeness.CoherenceSolver` for the current limit).
-- Pending that solver extension, we narrow the original postulate to
-- a `Structural`-restricted form whose hypothesis is exactly the
-- "symmetric monoidal coherence on the structural fragment" claim.
--
-- ## What this module exports
--
-- * `Structural`             ‚ÄĒ syntactic predicate "no `Agen` subterm".
-- * `nE-0‚ÜíStructural`        ‚ÄĒ `nE ‚ü™ g ‚üę ‚Č° 0 ‚Üí Structural g`,
--                              fully constructive.
-- * `Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm`
--                            ‚ÄĒ the *narrowed* postulate: any two
--                              structural terms of the same type with
--                              isomorphic translations are `‚ČąTerm`-equal
--                              at the `FreeMonoidal` level (i.e. `f ‚ČąTerm g`
--                              directly, no `decode-rel`/`bridge` wrapping).
--                              This is exactly Mac Lane's symmetric
--                              monoidal coherence theorem on the
--                              `id, őĽ, ŌĀ, őĪ, ŌÉ`-fragment.
-- * `Structural-coherence`   ‚ÄĒ derived: `decode-rel f ‚ČąTerm decode-rel g`,
--                              obtained from `Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm`
--                              by passing through `decode-roundtrip-rel`
--                              and the `bridge`-congruence.
-- * `decode-rel-resp-‚ČÖŠīī-atomic-compound-0E` ‚ÄĒ the original lemma,
--                              derived from the above ingredients
--                              together with the `Atomic ‚áí Structural`
--                              fact.
--
-- ## Why this narrowing is strict
--
-- The original postulate had conclusion `decode-rel f ‚ČąTerm decode-rel g`,
-- whose unfolding involves `bridge`, `unflatten-flatten-‚Čą`, and the
-- structural recursion of `decode-rel` through `‚ąė` and `‚äó‚āĀ`.  The
-- narrowed conclusion `f ‚ČąTerm g` lives purely in the free symmetric
-- monoidal category over the signature, with no decode plumbing ‚ÄĒ it
-- is exactly the statement of categorical coherence for the
-- non-generator (a.k.a. `Structural`) fragment.
--
-- The derivation back to the original form uses only existing
-- constructive lemmas:
--   * `decode-roundtrip-rel f : decode-rel f ‚ČąTerm bridge f`     (proved)
--   * `decode-roundtrip-rel g : decode-rel g ‚ČąTerm bridge g`     (proved)
--   * `bridge` is a congruence wrt `‚ČąTerm`                       (1-line proof)
-- so the original lemma is `decode-roundtrip-rel f ; bridge-cong ; sym (decode-roundtrip-rel g)`.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

