-- Narrowed postulate: symmetric-monoidal coherence on the structural
-- fragment, at the `FreeMonoidal` level.
--
-- This is the *minimal* postulate needed to discharge the original
-- `decode-rel-resp-‚ČÖŠīī-atomic-compound-0E`.  It is the statement of
-- Mac Lane's symmetric monoidal coherence theorem on the structural
-- (i.e. generator-free) sub-language: any two `Structural` HomTerms
-- of the same type whose hypergraph translations are isomorphic are
-- equal in the free symmetric monoidal category.
--
-- All `decode-rel`/`bridge`/`unflatten`-flavoured plumbing has been
-- factored out: the postulate conclusion is the plain `_‚ČąTerm_`
-- equality between two `HomTerm A B`s built from
-- `id, őĽ‚áí, őĽ‚áź, ŌĀ‚áí, ŌĀ‚áź, őĪ‚áí, őĪ‚áź, ŌÉ, _‚ąė_, _‚äó‚āĀ_`.  The constructive
-- discharge ultimately requires extending
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver` (currently Mac Lane only) to
-- handle ŌÉ via permutation tracking ‚ÄĒ see the header for the path.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Extract the underlying permutation of a structural HomTerm.
--
-- A 0-edge hypergraph IS a permutation (with labels) between its boundary
-- atom lists.  We extract this permutation by structural induction on
-- `Structural`, using only the propositional permutation combinators
-- (`refl`, `prep`, `swap`, `trans`) and standard list-permutation lemmas
-- (`++-comm`, `++-assoc`, `++-identity ≥`, `++‚Āļ`).
--
-- The directions:
--   * `id        : A ‚Üí A`              ‚Ü¶ refl
--   * `őĽ‚áí : I‚äóA ‚Üí A`,  `őĽ‚áź : A ‚Üí I‚äóA`  ‚Ü¶ refl     ([] ++ xs ‚Č° xs definitionally)
--   * `ŌĀ‚áí : A‚äóI ‚Üí A`                   ‚Ü¶ ++-identity ≥
--   * `ŌĀ‚áź : A ‚Üí A‚äóI`                   ‚Ü¶ sym (++-identity ≥)
--   * `őĪ‚áí : (A‚äóB)‚äóC ‚Üí A‚äó(B‚äóC)`         ‚Ü¶ ‚Ü≠-reflexive (++-assoc)
--   * `őĪ‚áź : A‚äó(B‚äóC) ‚Üí (A‚äóB)‚äóC`         ‚Ü¶ sym
--   * `ŌÉ  : A‚äóB ‚Üí B‚äóA`                 ‚Ü¶ ++-comm
--   * `_‚ąė_`                            ‚Ü¶ Perm.trans (note: h ‚ąė k goes k then h)
--   * `_‚äó‚āĀ_`                           ‚Ü¶ PermProp.++‚Āļ

Structural-to-perm
  : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Structural f ‚Üí flatten A ‚Ü≠ flatten B
Structural-to-perm (structural-id {A}) = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm structural-őĽ‚áí        = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm structural-őĽ‚áź        = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm (structural-ŌĀ‚áí {A})  = PermProp.++-identity ≥ (flatten A)
Structural-to-perm (structural-ŌĀ‚áź {A})  = Perm.‚Ü≠-sym (PermProp.++-identity ≥ (flatten A))
Structural-to-perm (structural-őĪ‚áí {A} {B} {C}) =
  Perm.‚Ü≠-reflexive (Data.List.Properties.++-assoc (flatten A) (flatten B) (flatten C))
Structural-to-perm (structural-őĪ‚áź {A} {B} {C}) =
  Perm.‚Ü≠-sym (Perm.‚Ü≠-reflexive (Data.List.Properties.++-assoc (flatten A) (flatten B) (flatten C)))
Structural-to-perm (structural-ŌÉ {A} {B}) =
  PermProp.++-comm (flatten A) (flatten B)
Structural-to-perm (structural-‚ąė sh sk) =
  Perm.trans (Structural-to-perm sk) (Structural-to-perm sh)
Structural-to-perm (structural-‚äó sh sk) =
  PermProp.++‚Āļ (Structural-to-perm sh) (Structural-to-perm sk)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Narrowed postulate: symmetric-monoidal coherence on the structural
-- fragment.
--
-- An earlier version of this file attempted a further split into
--
--   * `perm-eq-from-iso : ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę ‚Üí Structural-to-perm sf ‚Č° Structural-to-perm sg`
--   * `Structural-coherence-from-perm-eq : ‚Ä¶ ‚Č° ‚Ä¶ ‚Üí f ‚ČąTerm g`
--
-- and derived `Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm` from the two.  That split
-- is **unsound** in its propositional-equality form:
-- `Data.List.Relation.Binary.Permutation.Propositional._‚Ü≠_` is *not*
-- a thin relation ‚ÄĒ `Perm.refl` and `Perm.trans Perm.refl Perm.refl`
-- are distinct constructors despite witnessing the same underlying
-- list permutation.  Concrete counter-example: `f = id`, `sf =
-- structural-id`, `g = id ‚ąė id`, `sg = structural-‚ąė structural-id
-- structural-id` give `Structural-to-perm sf = Perm.refl` while
-- `Structural-to-perm sg = Perm.trans Perm.refl Perm.refl`, which are
-- *not* `_‚Č°_`, yet the corresponding hypergraphs are isomorphic.  So
-- the `perm-eq-from-iso` half could never be discharged as stated.
--
-- Reverting to a single postulate restores soundness: this is exactly
-- the statement of Mac Lane's symmetric monoidal coherence theorem on
-- the structural (i.e. generator-free) sub-language.  The constructive
-- discharge ultimately requires extending
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver` (currently Mac Lane only) to
-- handle ŌÉ via permutation tracking.
--
-- The constructive `Structural-to-perm` helper above is retained: it
-- is a useful and correct definition, and would feed into a future
-- model-theoretic discharge that interprets `FreeMonoidal` in a
-- category where structural morphisms are quotiented to bare list
-- permutations.

-- Splitting via `HasSigma?` exposes the ŌÉ-free (Mac Lane) sub-case as
-- a strictly narrower postulate that is mechanically dischargeable by
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver.solveM` once a variable-
-- indexing encoder is written (one Vec slot per distinct `Var x` atom
-- appearing in `A`/`B`).  The ŌÉ-containing residual is the genuine
-- remaining content ‚ÄĒ requires extending `solveM` to the symmetric
-- fragment.  Under the iso hypothesis the ŌÉ-free case has identity-
-- forced boundary ŌÜ, so Mac Lane coherence applies directly.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Constructive discharge plumbing for the ŌÉ-free case via
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver.solveM`.
--
-- We instantiate the Solver at the *target* monoidal category
-- `(FreeMonoidal, Monoidal-FreeMonoidal)` itself: use it as a *proof*
-- tool, not as an evaluator into another category.  The Vec
-- `vars : Vec ObjTerm n` provides the per-atom mapping; atom `Fin i`
-- in the solver's `FreeMonoidal` interprets as `lookup vars i`, an
-- `ObjTerm` of the surrounding APROP free monoidal category.
--
-- Encoder pipeline (constructive parts below):
--   1. `objAtoms : ObjTerm ‚Üí List X` collects `Var x` atoms.
--   2. `idx : (xs : List X) (x : X) ‚Üí Fin (length xs)` lookup
--      (using `_‚ČüX_`); on miss returns the last slot (safe fallback,
--      not used in the well-typed branch).
--   3. `varsOf : List X ‚Üí ‚ąÉ Vec ObjTerm` produces the encoder's Vec.
--
-- Bridging the solver's `Fin n`-based `FreeMonoidal` back to the
-- surrounding APROP `FreeMonoidal` (which is over `X` with `Symm`
-- variant) requires `subst`-plumbing through two distinct
-- `FreeMonoidal` instantiations.  We leave the bridge as a narrow
-- postulate `enc-faithful` below ‚ÄĒ strictly weaker than the original
-- `-noŌÉ` claim because it is the *purely structural* soundness of the
-- Mac Lane encoder, no ŌÉ involved.

-- Collect `Var x` atoms from an ObjTerm.
objAtoms : ObjTerm ‚Üí List X
objAtoms unit     = []
objAtoms (A ‚äó‚āÄ B) = objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B
objAtoms (Var x)  = x ‚ą∑ []

-- Index of x in xs (with safe fallback to `zero` of `Fin (suc (length xs))`).
idxFin : (xs : List X) (x : X) ‚Üí Fin (suc (length xs))
idxFin []       x = zero
idxFin (y ‚ą∑ ys) x with x ‚ČüX y
... | yes _ = zero
... | no  _ = suc (idxFin ys x)

-- Build a Vec of ObjTerm of length `suc (length xs)` from xs, padding
-- with `unit` at the sentinel slot.
varsVec : (xs : List X) ‚Üí Vec ObjTerm (suc (length xs))
varsVec []       = unit ‚ą∑‚ĪĹ []‚ĪĹ
varsVec (x ‚ą∑ xs) = Var x ‚ą∑‚ĪĹ varsVec xs

-- Instantiate the Mac Lane coherence solver at the surrounding
-- FreeMonoidal, with the per-pair Vec `varsVec (xsAll f g)`.
module _ {A B : ObjTerm} {f g : HomTerm A B} (nf : NoSigma f) (ng : NoSigma g) where

  -- Atoms that need to be in the Vec: those from A, B, and any
  -- intermediate types inside f, g.  For the Mac Lane fragment a
  -- conservative choice is `objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B` extended with
  -- atoms collected from each NoSigma sub-term's type indices.

  -- We collect via NoSigma so termination is on the structural witness.
  nosigmaAtoms : ‚ąÄ {A B} {h : HomTerm A B} ‚Üí NoSigma h ‚Üí List X
  nosigmaAtoms {A} {B} nosigma-id      = objAtoms A
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-őĽ‚áí {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-őĽ‚áź {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-ŌĀ‚áí {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-ŌĀ‚áź {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-őĪ‚áí {A'} {B'} {C'}) =
    objAtoms A' ++ objAtoms B' ++ objAtoms C'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-őĪ‚áź {A'} {B'} {C'}) =
    objAtoms A' ++ objAtoms B' ++ objAtoms C'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-‚ąė h k) = nosigmaAtoms h ++ nosigmaAtoms k
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-‚äó h k) = nosigmaAtoms h ++ nosigmaAtoms k

  xsAll : List X
  xsAll = objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B ++ nosigmaAtoms nf ++ nosigmaAtoms ng

  vars-fg : Vec ObjTerm (suc (length xsAll))
  vars-fg = varsVec xsAll

  -- Instantiate the Mac Lane coherence solver in the surrounding
  -- FreeMonoidal, using `vars-fg` as the per-atom interpretation.
  open import Categories.MonoidalCoherence using (module Solver)
  open import Categories.Category.Monoidal using (Monoidal)
  open Monoidal Monoidal-FreeMonoidal using () renaming () public

  module S = Solver
    record { U = FreeMonoidal ; monoidal = Monoidal-FreeMonoidal }
    {n = suc (length xsAll)} vars-fg


  -- Structural encoder: ObjTerm ‚Üí S.ObjTerm.  Atoms are indexed via
  -- `idxFin xsAll`; the sentinel slot (`unit`) catches misses but
  -- well-typed encoding never lands there.
  enc-Obj : ObjTerm ‚Üí S.ObjTerm
  enc-Obj unit     = S.unit
  enc-Obj (P ‚äó‚āÄ Q) = enc-Obj P S.‚äó‚āÄ enc-Obj Q
  enc-Obj (Var x)  = S.Var (idxFin xsAll x)

  -- Structural encoder on HomTerms: NoSigma ‚Üí S.HomTerm.  Defined by
  -- structural recursion on the `NoSigma` witness; each clause maps
  -- the APROP-side constructor to its solver-side counterpart.
  enc-Hom : ‚ąÄ {P Q} {h : HomTerm P Q}
          ‚Üí NoSigma h
          ‚Üí S.HomTerm (enc-Obj P) (enc-Obj Q)
  enc-Hom nosigma-id      = S.id
  enc-Hom nosigma-őĽ‚áí      = S.őĽ‚áí
  enc-Hom nosigma-őĽ‚áź      = S.őĽ‚áź
  enc-Hom nosigma-ŌĀ‚áí      = S.ŌĀ‚áí
  enc-Hom nosigma-ŌĀ‚áź      = S.ŌĀ‚áź
  enc-Hom nosigma-őĪ‚áí      = S.őĪ‚áí
  enc-Hom nosigma-őĪ‚áź      = S.őĪ‚áź
  enc-Hom (nosigma-‚ąė h k) = enc-Hom h S.‚ąė enc-Hom k
  enc-Hom (nosigma-‚äó h k) = enc-Hom h S.‚äó‚āĀ enc-Hom k

  -- The Solver's interpretation `‚ü¶ ef ‚üß‚āĀ` lives in APROP's
  -- FreeMonoidal: source `Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) : ObjTerm`, target similarly.
  -- `solveM ef eg : ‚ü¶ ef ‚üß‚āĀ ‚ČąTerm ‚ü¶ eg ‚üß‚āĀ` is precisely an APROP-side
  -- `_‚ČąTerm_` equation (Mac Lane coherence in the ŌÉ-free fragment).
  --
  -- To convert this into `f ‚ČąTerm g`, we need encoder-soundness:
  -- `f ‚ČąTerm Functor.F‚āĀ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nf)` and similarly for `g` (modulo
  -- equality `Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj A) ‚Č° A`).  Both lemmas are pure structural
  -- recursions, but discharging them requires bridging two
  -- `FreeMonoidal` instantiations and aligning `subst`s ‚ÄĒ left as a
  -- narrow self-contained postulate.

  -- Encoded pair (constructive output of the encoder).
  ef-built : S.HomTerm (enc-Obj A) (enc-Obj B)
  ef-built = enc-Hom nf

  eg-built : S.HomTerm (enc-Obj A) (enc-Obj B)
  eg-built = enc-Hom ng

  -- `solveM` discharges Mac Lane coherence in the ŌÉ-free Fin-indexed
  -- FreeMonoidal.  The return type uses the Solver's private
  -- `FreeFunctor` interpretation `‚ü¶_‚üß‚āĀ` (not re-exported by `Solver`
  -- with `public`).  We name the result and let Agda infer the type.
  --
  -- This call is the *constructive heart* of the ŌÉ-free coherence
  -- discharge: at this point all the categorical work is done.  The
  -- remaining work (`enc-bridge-to-f‚Čąg`) is purely the encoder's
  -- soundness reflection back into APROP's `_‚ČąTerm_`.
  solver-result : _
  solver-result = S.solveM ef-built eg-built

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  -- Encoder soundness: `Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) ‚Č° P` when atoms of P live in xsAll.
  --
  -- Below, `lookup-mem` is the heart: when `x ‚ąą xs` (witnessed by `Any`),
  -- the encoder round-trips `x` to `Var x`.  Then `enc-Obj-sound` is a
  -- straight structural induction on `P`, using `lookup-mem` at each
  -- `Var` leaf.

  -- Helper: lookup at the index produced by `idxFin` round-trips through
  -- the var-vector.  By induction on the membership witness.
  lookup-mem
    : (xs : List X) {x : X} (m : x ‚ąą xs)
    ‚Üí lookup (varsVec xs) (idxFin xs x) ‚Č° Var x
  lookup-mem (y ‚ą∑ ys) {x} (here refl) with x ‚ČüX y
  ... | yes _    = refl
  ... | no  x‚ČĘy  = ‚ä•-elim (x‚ČĘy refl)
  lookup-mem (y ‚ą∑ ys) {x} (there m) with x ‚ČüX y
  ... | yes refl = refl
  ... | no  _    = lookup-mem ys m

  -- A `Var` atom appearing inside `objAtoms P` is exactly an atom of P.
  -- For our use we need to convert "every atom of P is in xsAll" into
  -- the relevant membership witness.  We work with the simple sublist
  -- inclusion `objAtoms P ‚äÜ xsAll`.

  _‚äÜL_ : List X ‚Üí List X ‚Üí Set
  xs ‚äÜL ys = ‚ąÄ {x} ‚Üí x ‚ąą xs ‚Üí x ‚ąą ys

  -- Soundness of the object encoder, parameterised by membership.
  enc-Obj-sound
    : (P : ObjTerm)
    ‚Üí objAtoms P ‚äÜL xsAll
    ‚Üí Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) ‚Č° P
  enc-Obj-sound unit       _   = refl
  enc-Obj-sound (P ‚äó‚āÄ Q) sub =
    cong‚āā _‚äó‚āÄ_
      (enc-Obj-sound P (őĽ m ‚Üí sub (‚ąą-++ň° m)))
      (enc-Obj-sound Q (őĽ m ‚Üí sub (‚ąą-++ ≥ (objAtoms P) m)))
    where
      ‚ąą-++ň° : ‚ąÄ {x ys zs} ‚Üí x ‚ąą ys ‚Üí x ‚ąą (ys ++ zs)
      ‚ąą-++ň° (here px)  = here px
      ‚ąą-++ň° (there m)  = there (‚ąą-++ň° m)
      ‚ąą-++ ≥ : ‚ąÄ {x} (ys : List X) {zs} ‚Üí x ‚ąą zs ‚Üí x ‚ąą (ys ++ zs)
      ‚ąą-++ ≥ []        m = m
      ‚ąą-++ ≥ (y ‚ą∑ ys') m = there (‚ąą-++ ≥ ys' m)
  enc-Obj-sound (Var x) sub = lookup-mem xsAll (sub (here refl))

  -- xsAll begins with `objAtoms A`, so atoms of A are trivially in xsAll.
  -- Similarly, after the A-prefix it has objAtoms B, then the two
  -- nosigmaAtoms blocks.

  ‚ąą-++ň° : ‚ąÄ {x} {ys zs : List X} ‚Üí x ‚ąą ys ‚Üí x ‚ąą (ys ++ zs)
  ‚ąą-++ň° (here px)  = here px
  ‚ąą-++ň° (there m)  = there (‚ąą-++ň° m)
  ‚ąą-++ ≥ : ‚ąÄ {x} (ys : List X) {zs : List X} ‚Üí x ‚ąą zs ‚Üí x ‚ąą (ys ++ zs)
  ‚ąą-++ ≥ []        m = m
  ‚ąą-++ ≥ (y ‚ą∑ ys') m = there (‚ąą-++ ≥ ys' m)

  -- objAtoms A is the first block of xsAll.
  A-atoms-in-xsAll : objAtoms A ‚äÜL xsAll
  A-atoms-in-xsAll m = ‚ąą-++ň° m

  B-atoms-in-xsAll : objAtoms B ‚äÜL xsAll
  B-atoms-in-xsAll m = ‚ąą-++ ≥ (objAtoms A) (‚ąą-++ň° m)

  enc-Obj-sound-A : Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj A) ‚Č° A
  enc-Obj-sound-A = enc-Obj-sound A A-atoms-in-xsAll

  enc-Obj-sound-B : Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj B) ‚Č° B
  enc-Obj-sound-B = enc-Obj-sound B B-atoms-in-xsAll

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  -- Inclusion of every NoSigma sub-term's atoms into xsAll.  We thread
  -- this as a `Path` from a witness inside `nf`/`ng` down to xsAll.
  --
  -- For ‚ąė/‚äó we use the fact that `nosigmaAtoms` is additive across
  -- composition/tensor (the witness lives in either the left or right
  -- branch).  But really, only the LEAF nodes need direct membership ‚ÄĒ
  -- internal ‚ąė/‚äó nodes inherit recursively.  We therefore phrase
  -- `enc-Hom-sound` as: given that the source and target objAtoms are
  -- in xsAll, the encoder is sound; and at ‚ąė/‚äó we recurse with the
  -- intermediate type's atoms in xsAll (provided by the structural
  -- shape of nf, ng).

  -- For `nosigma-‚ąė {B = M} h k` we need atoms of M in xsAll.  In the
  -- `nf`/`ng` witnesses, the intermediate type M's atoms appear in the
  -- corresponding sub-term's nosigmaAtoms (every leaf inside h has type
  -- with M-related atoms covered).  Rather than thread the inclusion
  -- explicitly, we expose a structural-induction-friendly form that
  -- carries the source/target inclusions as parameters.

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  -- Hom encoder soundness (‚ČąTerm form, parameterised by atom-inclusions
  -- for the source and target types).
  --
  -- We package `Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) ‚Č° P` and similarly for Q, then state:
  --
  --   subst‚āā HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚āĀ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nh)) ‚Č° h
  --
  -- By induction on nh.  Base cases are immediate because
  -- `S.‚ü¶ S.id ‚üß‚āĀ`, `S.‚ü¶ S.őĽ‚áí ‚üß‚āĀ`, ..., reduce definitionally to the
  -- APROP-side constructors `id`, `őĽ‚áí`, ..., at the encoded source/
  -- target objects.  The `subst‚āā` collapses to `refl` after K-style
  -- reasoning on ObjTerm equality (justified by ObjTerm having
  -- decidable equality, hence UIP).

  -- For the ‚ąė/‚äó inductive cases we additionally need atom-inclusion
  -- for the intermediate type; these come from the structural form
  -- of the NoSigma sub-witness's source/target leaves.

  -- We expose only the specialised forms we need: encoder soundness
  -- specifically at f and at g (both `HomTerm A B`).  Their proofs use
  -- the postulate `enc-Hom-‚Č°-up-to-subst` below ‚ÄĒ the *narrowest*
  -- remaining gap, strictly about `subst` plumbing through a
  -- definitionally-trivial encoder.

  -- Discharge of `enc-Hom-sound-id`: any NoSigma term h is transported
  -- to itself by the encoder‚Äďdecoder round-trip.  Proof: induction on
  -- nh.  For each structural constructor, `F‚āĀ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom ‚Ä¶)`
  -- reduces definitionally to the corresponding APROP-side constructor,
  -- and the subst‚āā collapses via UIP on ObjTerm (provable from decidable
  -- atom equality `_‚Čü-ObjTerm_`) combined with J on a single object-arg
  -- equality (per constructor).
  private
    import Axiom.UniquenessOfIdentityProofs as UIP-mod
    open APROPSignatureDec sig-dec using (_‚Čü-ObjTerm_)
    module ObjTerm-UIP-mod = UIP-mod.Decidable‚áíUIP _‚Čü-ObjTerm_

    ObjTerm-UIP : ‚ąÄ {A B : ObjTerm} (p q : A ‚Č° B) ‚Üí p ‚Č° q
    ObjTerm-UIP = ObjTerm-UIP-mod.‚Č°-irrelevant

    -- Per-constructor coercion lemmas.  Each takes the source/target
    -- substitutions plus the underlying argument equalities (derived
    -- from sP/sQ via injectivity of `_‚äó‚āÄ_`), and reduces `subst‚āā`
    -- through the constructor to refl.

    id-coerce
      : ‚ąÄ {X Y : ObjTerm} (p q : X ‚Č° Y)
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm p q (id {X}) ‚Č° id {Y}
    id-coerce refl q with ObjTerm-UIP q refl
    ... | refl = refl

    őĽ‚áí-coerce
      : ‚ąÄ {X Y : ObjTerm} (p : unit ‚äó‚āÄ X ‚Č° unit ‚äó‚āÄ Y) (q : X ‚Č° Y)
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm p q (őĽ‚áí {X}) ‚Č° őĽ‚áí {Y}
    őĽ‚áí-coerce p refl with ObjTerm-UIP p refl
    ... | refl = refl

    őĽ‚áź-coerce
      : ‚ąÄ {X Y : ObjTerm} (p : X ‚Č° Y) (q : unit ‚äó‚āÄ X ‚Č° unit ‚äó‚āÄ Y)
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm p q (őĽ‚áź {X}) ‚Č° őĽ‚áź {Y}
    őĽ‚áź-coerce refl q with ObjTerm-UIP q refl
    ... | refl = refl

    ŌĀ‚áí-coerce
      : ‚ąÄ {X Y : ObjTerm} (p : X ‚äó‚āÄ unit ‚Č° Y ‚äó‚āÄ unit) (q : X ‚Č° Y)
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm p q (ŌĀ‚áí {X}) ‚Č° ŌĀ‚áí {Y}
    ŌĀ‚áí-coerce p refl with ObjTerm-UIP p refl
    ... | refl = refl

    ŌĀ‚áź-coerce
      : ‚ąÄ {X Y : ObjTerm} (p : X ‚Č° Y) (q : X ‚äó‚āÄ unit ‚Č° Y ‚äó‚āÄ unit)
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm p q (ŌĀ‚áź {X}) ‚Č° ŌĀ‚áź {Y}
    ŌĀ‚áź-coerce refl q with ObjTerm-UIP q refl
    ... | refl = refl

    őĪ‚áí-coerce
      : ‚ąÄ {X Y Z X' Y' Z' : ObjTerm}
          (sX : X ‚Č° X') (sY : Y ‚Č° Y') (sZ : Z ‚Č° Z')
          (p : (X ‚äó‚āÄ Y) ‚äó‚āÄ Z ‚Č° (X' ‚äó‚āÄ Y') ‚äó‚āÄ Z')
          (q : X ‚äó‚āÄ (Y ‚äó‚āÄ Z) ‚Č° X' ‚äó‚āÄ (Y' ‚äó‚āÄ Z'))
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm p q (őĪ‚áí {X} {Y} {Z}) ‚Č° őĪ‚áí {X'} {Y'} {Z'}
    őĪ‚áí-coerce refl refl refl p q
      with ObjTerm-UIP p refl | ObjTerm-UIP q refl
    ... | refl | refl = refl

    őĪ‚áź-coerce
      : ‚ąÄ {X Y Z X' Y' Z' : ObjTerm}
          (sX : X ‚Č° X') (sY : Y ‚Č° Y') (sZ : Z ‚Č° Z')
          (p : X ‚äó‚āÄ (Y ‚äó‚āÄ Z) ‚Č° X' ‚äó‚āÄ (Y' ‚äó‚āÄ Z'))
          (q : (X ‚äó‚āÄ Y) ‚äó‚āÄ Z ‚Č° (X' ‚äó‚āÄ Y') ‚äó‚āÄ Z')
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm p q (őĪ‚áź {X} {Y} {Z}) ‚Č° őĪ‚áź {X'} {Y'} {Z'}
    őĪ‚áź-coerce refl refl refl p q
      with ObjTerm-UIP p refl | ObjTerm-UIP q refl
    ... | refl | refl = refl

    -- Injectivity of `_‚äó‚āÄ_`.
    ‚äó-injň° : ‚ąÄ {A A' B B' : ObjTerm} ‚Üí (A ‚äó‚āÄ B) ‚Č° (A' ‚äó‚āÄ B') ‚Üí A ‚Č° A'
    ‚äó-injň° refl = refl

    ‚äó-inj ≥ : ‚ąÄ {A A' B B' : ObjTerm} ‚Üí (A ‚äó‚āÄ B) ‚Č° (A' ‚äó‚āÄ B') ‚Üí B ‚Č° B'
    ‚äó-inj ≥ refl = refl

    -- Push subst‚āā through `_‚ąė_`: it preserves composition, factored
    -- through an intermediate type's equality `sM`.
    ‚ąė-coerce
      : ‚ąÄ {X M Y X' M' Y' : ObjTerm}
          (h : HomTerm M Y) (k : HomTerm X M)
          (h' : HomTerm M' Y') (k' : HomTerm X' M')
          (sX : X ‚Č° X') (sM : M ‚Č° M') (sY : Y ‚Č° Y')
          (p : X ‚Č° X') (q : Y ‚Č° Y')
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm sM sY h ‚Č° h'
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm sX sM k ‚Č° k'
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm p q (h ‚ąė k) ‚Č° h' ‚ąė k'
    ‚ąė-coerce h k h' k' refl refl refl p q eh ek
      with ObjTerm-UIP p refl | ObjTerm-UIP q refl
    ... | refl | refl rewrite eh | ek = refl

    -- Push subst‚āā through `_‚äó‚āĀ_`.
    ‚äó-coerce
      : ‚ąÄ {A B C D A' B' C' D' : ObjTerm}
          (h : HomTerm A B) (k : HomTerm C D)
          (h' : HomTerm A' B') (k' : HomTerm C' D')
          (sA : A ‚Č° A') (sB : B ‚Č° B') (sC : C ‚Č° C') (sD : D ‚Č° D')
          (p : A ‚äó‚āÄ C ‚Č° A' ‚äó‚āÄ C') (q : B ‚äó‚āÄ D ‚Č° B' ‚äó‚āÄ D')
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm sA sB h ‚Č° h'
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm sC sD k ‚Č° k'
      ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm p q (h ‚äó‚āĀ k) ‚Č° h' ‚äó‚āĀ k'
    ‚äó-coerce h k h' k' refl refl refl refl p q eh ek
      with ObjTerm-UIP p refl | ObjTerm-UIP q refl
    ... | refl | refl rewrite eh | ek = refl

  -- Inclusion bookkeeping: every NoSigma sub-term's source and target
  -- objAtoms are contained in its `nosigmaAtoms`.  Combined with an
  -- outer "this nh's nosigmaAtoms ‚äÜ xsAll" hypothesis, we can recover
  -- the intermediate-type equality at every recursive step.

  private
    ‚äÜL-trans : ‚ąÄ {xs ys zs : List X} ‚Üí xs ‚äÜL ys ‚Üí ys ‚äÜL zs ‚Üí xs ‚äÜL zs
    ‚äÜL-trans f g m = g (f m)

    ‚äÜL-++ň° : ‚ąÄ {xs ys zs : List X} ‚Üí xs ‚äÜL ys ‚Üí xs ‚äÜL (ys ++ zs)
    ‚äÜL-++ň° f m = ‚ąą-++ň° (f m)

    ‚äÜL-++ ≥ : ‚ąÄ {xs} (ys : List X) {zs : List X} ‚Üí xs ‚äÜL zs ‚Üí xs ‚äÜL (ys ++ zs)
    ‚äÜL-++ ≥ ys f m = ‚ąą-++ ≥ ys (f m)

    ‚äÜL-refl : ‚ąÄ {xs : List X} ‚Üí xs ‚äÜL xs
    ‚äÜL-refl m = m

    objAtoms-‚äó‚āÄ : ‚ąÄ A B ‚Üí objAtoms (A ‚äó‚āÄ B) ‚äÜL (objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B)
    objAtoms-‚äó‚āÄ A B = ‚äÜL-refl

    -- src-atoms / tgt-atoms of a NoSigma witness are included in its nosigmaAtoms.
    nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ : ‚ąÄ {P Q} {h : HomTerm P Q} (nh : NoSigma h)
                      ‚Üí objAtoms P ‚äÜL nosigmaAtoms nh
    nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ : ‚ąÄ {P Q} {h : HomTerm P Q} (nh : NoSigma h)
                      ‚Üí objAtoms Q ‚äÜL nosigmaAtoms nh

    nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ (nosigma-id {A}) = ‚äÜL-refl
    -- src of őĽ‚áí is unit ‚äó‚āÄ A; objAtoms = [] ++ objAtoms A = objAtoms A
    nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ (nosigma-őĽ‚áí {A}) m = m
    nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ (nosigma-őĽ‚áź {A}) m = m
    nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ (nosigma-ŌĀ‚áí {A}) {x} m = aux (objAtoms A) m
      where
        aux : ‚ąÄ (xs : List X) {x} ‚Üí x ‚ąą (xs ++ []) ‚Üí x ‚ąą xs
        aux []       ()
        aux (y ‚ą∑ ys) (here px) = here px
        aux (y ‚ą∑ ys) (there m') = there (aux ys m')
    nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ (nosigma-ŌĀ‚áź {A}) m = m
    nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ (nosigma-őĪ‚áí {A} {B} {C}) m = őĪ‚áí-src m
      where
        -- src = (A‚äóB)‚äóC, objAtoms = (objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B) ++ objAtoms C
        -- tgt of nosigmaAtoms = objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B ++ objAtoms C
        őĪ‚áí-src : ((objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B) ++ objAtoms C) ‚äÜL (objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B ++ objAtoms C)
        őĪ‚áí-src m' = ++-assoc-‚Üí (objAtoms A) (objAtoms B) (objAtoms C) m'
          where
            ++-assoc-‚Üí : ‚ąÄ (xs ys zs : List X) {x}
                       ‚Üí x ‚ąą ((xs ++ ys) ++ zs) ‚Üí x ‚ąą (xs ++ ys ++ zs)
            ++-assoc-‚Üí []       ys zs m'' = m''
            ++-assoc-‚Üí (x ‚ą∑ xs') ys zs (here px) = here px
            ++-assoc-‚Üí (x ‚ą∑ xs') ys zs (there m'') = there (++-assoc-‚Üí xs' ys zs m'')
    nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ (nosigma-őĪ‚áź {A} {B} {C}) m = m  -- src = A‚äó(B‚äóC), same flattening
    nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ (nosigma-‚ąė h k) = ‚äÜL-++ ≥ (nosigmaAtoms h) (nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ k)
    nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ (nosigma-‚äó {A} {B} {C} {D} h k) =
      atoms-split-src {A} {C} (nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ h) (nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ k)
      where
        -- Generic: split membership across `xs ++ ys`.
        split-‚ąą : ‚ąÄ {x} (xs ys : List X) ‚Üí x ‚ąą (xs ++ ys) ‚Üí (x ‚ąą xs) ‚äé (x ‚ąą ys)
        split-‚ąą []       ys m            = inj‚āā m
        split-‚ąą (y ‚ą∑ ys') zs (here px)   = inj‚āĀ (here px)
        split-‚ąą (y ‚ą∑ ys') zs (there m')  with split-‚ąą ys' zs m'
        ... | inj‚āĀ m'' = inj‚āĀ (there m'')
        ... | inj‚āā m'' = inj‚āā m''

        atoms-split-src
          : ‚ąÄ {A C : ObjTerm} {hA hB : List X}
          ‚Üí objAtoms A ‚äÜL hA ‚Üí objAtoms C ‚äÜL hB
          ‚Üí objAtoms (A ‚äó‚āÄ C) ‚äÜL (hA ++ hB)
        atoms-split-src {A} {C} {hA} {hB} fa fc {x} m with split-‚ąą (objAtoms A) (objAtoms C) m
        ... | inj‚āĀ mA = ‚ąą-++ň° (fa mA)
        ... | inj‚āā mC = ‚ąą-++ ≥ hA (fc mC)

    nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ (nosigma-id {A}) = ‚äÜL-refl
    nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ (nosigma-őĽ‚áí {A}) = ‚äÜL-refl
    nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ (nosigma-őĽ‚áź {A}) m = m
    nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ (nosigma-ŌĀ‚áí {A}) = ‚äÜL-refl
    nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ (nosigma-ŌĀ‚áź {A}) {x} m = aux (objAtoms A) m
      where
        aux : ‚ąÄ (xs : List X) {x} ‚Üí x ‚ąą (xs ++ []) ‚Üí x ‚ąą xs
        aux []       ()
        aux (y ‚ą∑ ys) (here px) = here px
        aux (y ‚ą∑ ys) (there m') = there (aux ys m')
    nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ (nosigma-őĪ‚áí {A} {B} {C}) m = m  -- tgt is A‚äó(B‚äóC)
    nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ (nosigma-őĪ‚áź {A} {B} {C}) m = őĪ‚áź-tgt m
      where
        őĪ‚áź-tgt : ((objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B) ++ objAtoms C) ‚äÜL (objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B ++ objAtoms C)
        őĪ‚áź-tgt m' = ++-assoc-‚Üí (objAtoms A) (objAtoms B) (objAtoms C) m'
          where
            ++-assoc-‚Üí : ‚ąÄ (xs ys zs : List X) {x}
                       ‚Üí x ‚ąą ((xs ++ ys) ++ zs) ‚Üí x ‚ąą (xs ++ ys ++ zs)
            ++-assoc-‚Üí []       ys zs m'' = m''
            ++-assoc-‚Üí (x ‚ą∑ xs') ys zs (here px) = here px
            ++-assoc-‚Üí (x ‚ą∑ xs') ys zs (there m'') = there (++-assoc-‚Üí xs' ys zs m'')
    nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ (nosigma-‚ąė h k) = ‚äÜL-++ň° (nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ h)
    nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ (nosigma-‚äó {A} {B} {C} {D} h k) =
      atoms-split-tgt {B} {D} (nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ h) (nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ k)
      where
        split-‚ąą : ‚ąÄ {x} (xs ys : List X) ‚Üí x ‚ąą (xs ++ ys) ‚Üí (x ‚ąą xs) ‚äé (x ‚ąą ys)
        split-‚ąą []       ys m            = inj‚āā m
        split-‚ąą (y ‚ą∑ ys') zs (here px)   = inj‚āĀ (here px)
        split-‚ąą (y ‚ą∑ ys') zs (there m')  with split-‚ąą ys' zs m'
        ... | inj‚āĀ m'' = inj‚āĀ (there m'')
        ... | inj‚āā m'' = inj‚āā m''

        atoms-split-tgt
          : ‚ąÄ {B D : ObjTerm} {hA hB : List X}
          ‚Üí objAtoms B ‚äÜL hA ‚Üí objAtoms D ‚äÜL hB
          ‚Üí objAtoms (B ‚äó‚āÄ D) ‚äÜL (hA ++ hB)
        atoms-split-tgt {B} {D} {hA} {hB} fa fc {x} m with split-‚ąą (objAtoms B) (objAtoms D) m
        ... | inj‚āĀ mB = ‚ąą-++ň° (fa mB)
        ... | inj‚āā mD = ‚ąą-++ ≥ hA (fc mD)

    -- Intermediate-type equality for the ‚ąė case: in `nosigma-‚ąė h k`,
    -- given an outer inclusion `nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-‚ąė h k) ‚äÜL xsAll`,
    -- the intermediate type M = tgt k = src h has objAtoms covered.
    inter-eq
      : ‚ąÄ {P Q} {h : HomTerm P Q} (nh : NoSigma h)
      ‚Üí nosigmaAtoms nh ‚äÜL xsAll
      ‚Üí Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) ‚Č° P
    inter-eq {P} nh inc = enc-Obj-sound P (‚äÜL-trans (nosigmaAtoms-src‚äÜ nh) inc)

    inter-eq-tgt
      : ‚ąÄ {P Q} {h : HomTerm P Q} (nh : NoSigma h)
      ‚Üí nosigmaAtoms nh ‚äÜL xsAll
      ‚Üí Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj Q) ‚Č° Q
    inter-eq-tgt {Q = Q} nh inc = enc-Obj-sound Q (‚äÜL-trans (nosigmaAtoms-tgt‚äÜ nh) inc)

  -- The main lemma.  Now parameterised by an inclusion proof so we can
  -- access intermediate-type equalities in `‚ąė` recursive cases.
  enc-Hom-sound-id-inc
    : ‚ąÄ {P Q} {h : HomTerm P Q} (nh : NoSigma h)
      (inc : nosigmaAtoms nh ‚äÜL xsAll)
      (sP : Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) ‚Č° P)
      (sQ : Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj Q) ‚Č° Q)
    ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚āĀ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nh)) ‚Č° h
  enc-Hom-sound-id-inc (nosigma-id {A})            inc sP sQ = id-coerce sP sQ
  enc-Hom-sound-id-inc (nosigma-őĽ‚áí {A})            inc sP sQ = őĽ‚áí-coerce sP sQ
  enc-Hom-sound-id-inc (nosigma-őĽ‚áź {A})            inc sP sQ = őĽ‚áź-coerce sP sQ
  enc-Hom-sound-id-inc (nosigma-ŌĀ‚áí {A})            inc sP sQ = ŌĀ‚áí-coerce sP sQ
  enc-Hom-sound-id-inc (nosigma-ŌĀ‚áź {A})            inc sP sQ = ŌĀ‚áź-coerce sP sQ
  enc-Hom-sound-id-inc (nosigma-őĪ‚áí {A} {B} {C})    inc sP sQ =
    őĪ‚áí-coerce (‚äó-injň° (‚äó-injň° sP)) (‚äó-inj ≥ (‚äó-injň° sP)) (‚äó-inj ≥ sP) sP sQ
  enc-Hom-sound-id-inc (nosigma-őĪ‚áź {A} {B} {C})    inc sP sQ =
    őĪ‚áź-coerce (‚äó-injň° sP) (‚äó-injň° (‚äó-inj ≥ sP)) (‚äó-inj ≥ (‚äó-inj ≥ sP)) sP sQ
  enc-Hom-sound-id-inc (nosigma-‚ąė {A} {M} {C} h k) inc sP sQ =
    let
      inc-h : nosigmaAtoms h ‚äÜL xsAll
      inc-h m = inc (‚ąą-++ň° m)
      inc-k : nosigmaAtoms k ‚äÜL xsAll
      inc-k m = inc (‚ąą-++ ≥ (nosigmaAtoms h) m)
      sM : Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj M) ‚Č° M
      sM = inter-eq-tgt k inc-k  -- tgt of k = M
    in ‚ąė-coerce _ _ _ _ sP sM sQ sP sQ
         (enc-Hom-sound-id-inc h inc-h sM sQ)
         (enc-Hom-sound-id-inc k inc-k sP sM)
  enc-Hom-sound-id-inc (nosigma-‚äó {A} {B} {C} {D} h k) inc sP sQ =
    let
      inc-h : nosigmaAtoms h ‚äÜL xsAll
      inc-h m = inc (‚ąą-++ň° m)
      inc-k : nosigmaAtoms k ‚äÜL xsAll
      inc-k m = inc (‚ąą-++ ≥ (nosigmaAtoms h) m)
    in ‚äó-coerce _ _ _ _
         (‚äó-injň° sP) (‚äó-injň° sQ) (‚äó-inj ≥ sP) (‚äó-inj ≥ sQ) sP sQ
         (enc-Hom-sound-id-inc h inc-h (‚äó-injň° sP) (‚äó-injň° sQ))
         (enc-Hom-sound-id-inc k inc-k (‚äó-inj ≥ sP) (‚äó-inj ≥ sQ))

  -- Inclusions for the top-level nf and ng in xsAll = objAtoms A ++
  -- objAtoms B ++ nosigmaAtoms nf ++ nosigmaAtoms ng.
  private
    nf-inclusion : nosigmaAtoms nf ‚äÜL xsAll
    nf-inclusion m = ‚ąą-++ ≥ (objAtoms A) (‚ąą-++ ≥ (objAtoms B) (‚ąą-++ň° m))

    ng-inclusion : nosigmaAtoms ng ‚äÜL xsAll
    ng-inclusion m = ‚ąą-++ ≥ (objAtoms A) (‚ąą-++ ≥ (objAtoms B) (‚ąą-++ ≥ (nosigmaAtoms nf) m))

  -- Lift the propositional encoder-soundness into ‚ČąTerm.  Specialised
  -- to nh = nf and nh = ng (the only consumers), where the inclusion
  -- `nosigmaAtoms nh ‚äÜL xsAll` is structurally available.
  enc-Hom-sound-‚Čą-nf
    : (sP : Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj A) ‚Č° A) (sQ : Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj B) ‚Č° B)
    ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚āĀ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nf)) ‚ČąTerm f
  enc-Hom-sound-‚Čą-nf sP sQ
    rewrite enc-Hom-sound-id-inc nf nf-inclusion sP sQ = ‚Čą-Term-refl

  enc-Hom-sound-‚Čą-ng
    : (sP : Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj A) ‚Č° A) (sQ : Functor.F‚āÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj B) ‚Č° B)
    ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚āĀ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom ng)) ‚ČąTerm g
  enc-Hom-sound-‚Čą-ng sP sQ
    rewrite enc-Hom-sound-id-inc ng ng-inclusion sP sQ = ‚Čą-Term-refl

  -- The discharge of the ŌÉ-free Structural coherence postulate:
  -- combine encoder soundness with `solver-result`.  All three pieces
  -- live in `HomTerm A B` after the subst-transports of
  -- `enc-Obj-sound-{A,B}`.

  noŌÉ-discharge : f ‚ČąTerm g
  noŌÉ-discharge = ‚Čą-Term-trans (‚Čą-Term-sym sound-f)
                   (‚Čą-Term-trans subst-eq sound-g)
    where
      sP = enc-Obj-sound-A
      sQ = enc-Obj-sound-B

      sound-f : subst‚āā HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚āĀ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nf)) ‚ČąTerm f
      sound-f = enc-Hom-sound-‚Čą-nf sP sQ

      sound-g : subst‚āā HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚āĀ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom ng)) ‚ČąTerm g
      sound-g = enc-Hom-sound-‚Čą-ng sP sQ

      -- Push solver-result through subst‚āā: subst‚āā is a congruence
      -- for ‚ČąTerm (with the same indices on both sides).
      subst‚āā-cong-‚ČąTerm
        : ‚ąÄ {P Q P' Q'} (eP : P ‚Č° P') (eQ : Q ‚Č° Q')
          {h k : HomTerm P Q} ‚Üí h ‚ČąTerm k
        ‚Üí subst‚āā HomTerm eP eQ h ‚ČąTerm subst‚āā HomTerm eP eQ k
      subst‚āā-cong-‚ČąTerm refl refl eq = eq

      subst-eq
        : subst‚āā HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚āĀ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nf))
        ‚ČąTerm subst‚āā HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚āĀ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom ng))
      subst-eq = subst‚āā-cong-‚ČąTerm sP sQ solver-result

-- Discharge of the previously-postulated ŌÉ-free coherence claim, now
-- via the module-internal `noŌÉ-discharge`.

Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm-noŌÉ
  : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí NoSigma f ‚Üí NoSigma g
  ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę
  ‚Üí f ‚ČąTerm g
Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm-noŌÉ {f = f} {g = g} nf ng _ = noŌÉ-discharge nf ng

postulate
  Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm-ŌÉ
    : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
    ‚Üí Structural f ‚Üí Structural g
    ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę
    ‚Üí f ‚ČąTerm g

-- Dispatch: ŌÉ-free √ó ŌÉ-free goes to the Mac Lane sub-postulate; any
-- ŌÉ-containing pair goes to the symmetric residual.
Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm
  : ‚ąÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Structural f ‚Üí Structural g
  ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚üę ‚ČÖŠīī ‚ü™ g ‚üę
  ‚Üí f ‚ČąTerm g
Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm sf sg iso with HasSigma? sf | HasSigma? sg
... | inj‚āĀ nf | inj‚āĀ ng = Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm-noŌÉ nf ng iso
... | _       | _       = Structural-coherence-‚ČąTerm-ŌÉ   sf sg iso

